      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of meritocracy is a dangerous fiction that actively masks entrenched racial bias. It falsely presumes a level playing field that simply does not exist, ignoring how systemic racism pre-determines life outcomes based on race, not effort. When wealth is concentrated along racial lines, \"hard work\" is often just the act of surviving oppressive structures, not achieving success within them. Therefore, claiming meritocracy is simply an ideological defense mechanism used to justify the status quo of racial disparity.",
